The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Wednesday, February 18, 2004 				 All for a cause
Showcasing the multi-faceted artistic genius of the three celebrities  Louis Banks, Sonia Sehgal and Bibi Russell  Spandan, in association with Hyatt Regency, Calcutta, presents a unique evening of fashion, music and art. The event, presented in aid of Anubhav-Kolkata, a social welfare project for the benefit of underprivileged children and the aged, will see an interesting blend of music, art and fashion. Jazz and Indo-Jazz fusion music, the core of Louis Banks performance, will be complemented by an art display of some of his finest impressionistic canvasses. Two of Banks works will also be auctioned. Well-known singer Sonia Sehgal will render some of her most popular numbers, while Bibi Russells exotic creations, illustrating the designers commitment to preserve the heritage and traditions of Bangladesh, will find expression in an awesome fashion show by 11 professional models.																								Event: An evening of fashion, music and art																								When: Today at 7 pm																								Where: The Ballroom, Hyatt Regency
